<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-D8F4A0EA-5E9A-4C9A-8EC6-8982C873948E" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-D8F4A0EA-5E9A-4C9A-8EC6-8982C873948E" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">07 How to identify a leakage of the pressure system</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-0E3E2CA2-5349-4FAF-80F5-347AA9765351"><p class="- topic/p "> This document describes how to identify a leakage of the air pressure system. (Air Pressure Supply Unit (APSU, (long) tube, manifold, filter, hose to the printhead, printhead). 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-F8EE43B1-36AF-4F86-8810-3B686A03AF19" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_7D2D5E82D5044E4D806F1126D45FFCBC" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_3A6A780FCE62425DA268B914DC7D2D21" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the ink supply unit. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="02DISA012" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1C874C66-3A17-4AC4-886B-753A1A37D196.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 02 Open the ink system?>02 Open the ink system</xref> 
</p></li></ul></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_88D5352595F642AFA44E04454C82A41C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_09DFB8A70D17453A89E1C6516B69232F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T25 
</p></li><li id="LI_81BD581B2AB94DF7AD868492835F1346" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Wear 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex 
</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Clamp (bag with 10 clamps): 1060115758. Use only this type of clamps. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Blanking plug 6 (1070066061) 
</p><fig id="GUID-E7DDBF0E-94FB-4C7F-BEF2-3EB0916DF6EE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-763340DE-510B-4258-BA5C-C0C860B3AD96-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-763340DE-510B-4258-BA5C-C0C860B3AD96-low.png"/></fig></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-2D7D94A0-B26C-4C0B-B6A3-20C8621663A2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Wear safety glasses if splashed can occur. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-B32F9B13-799D-4FB6-8BCF-694693538A10" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-BB8A9B56-5934-430F-B18D-BF274963F830-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-BB8A9B56-5934-430F-B18D-BF274963F830-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> In the first step the complete pressure system is tested. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In the next steps all separate functions are tested. 
</p></section><section id="SECTION_43C265C317124960971C8DC89357C70F" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_1DBCBCA7090F42239EA97BBE973A138D" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-5C831DFA-8745-4849-A889-14C47F0AE22C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">This test only works in a warm SDS test. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Test completed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No air pressure leakage. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Test the APSU:</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Place a clamp on the air hose just above the Air Pressure Supply Unit (APSU) or use a blanking plug 6 to block the hose. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-CEB2277E-BF60-4879-B3A7-0DAD6AD728C2" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">With clamp</title><image href="GUID-AB3CD407-ABC5-4246-8BD7-5784005469B6-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AB3CD407-ABC5-4246-8BD7-5784005469B6-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-DDA5E90E-53EC-4E7D-BC14-F34350AAE267" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title ">with blanking plug 6</title><image href="GUID-D778494F-3447-4BE0-874E-B0E3162B0F7F-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D778494F-3447-4BE0-874E-B0E3162B0F7F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-7945FD43-0D4A-4E60-84D7-BA9F2E16CFCB" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test failed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the Air Pressure Supply Unit (APSU). 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See 
<xref keyref="07DISA001" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-84FA58C8-6733-4EB2-BEE5-800D115C8054.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text xref?>07 How to remove the Air Pressure Supply Unit (APSU)</xref> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the clamp (above the Air Pressure Supply Unit (APSU)). 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Place a red clamp on the air tube near the printheads (on the part with the sleeve). 
</p><fig id="GUID-0043C906-67A5-4A99-90C0-43EBB8620329" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E0CBBD17-6A9D-4CE2-91C9-152761273297-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E0CBBD17-6A9D-4CE2-91C9-152761273297-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5F9CD0AB-5132-407B-9EB3-BBF2FD90C0EF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A8E535E3-437C-45B6-825D-D7E570928836-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A8E535E3-437C-45B6-825D-D7E570928836-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-D75A954C-AE44-4BE2-9723-EBC3DB91A8D1" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Test failed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Replace the Air tube. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the red clamp. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">8 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Test Manifold 1: 
</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Place 2 red clamps on the air tube of printhead 1 (White) (on the part with the sleeve) and the air hose between manifold 1 and 2. 
</p><fig id="GUID-194125E8-3E73-426C-AB68-52D1C3A7D393" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-E4F1FD76-5862-48F2-9471-D74F3A5A7144-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-E4F1FD76-5862-48F2-9471-D74F3A5A7144-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-483AA56B-3397-4E05-ADB2-782D2EFCE9CA" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-03E302A6-DA3C-4459-A5E6-EF656C908960-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-03E302A6-DA3C-4459-A5E6-EF656C908960-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-DE679A5B-14B9-476A-99B9-704F50C82849" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test failed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Replace the manifold 1. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 2 red clamps. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Test Manifold 2</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Place 4 red clamps on the air tube of printhead 1 (White), printhead 3 &amp; 4 (Magenta &amp; Yellow) (on the part with the sleeve) and the air hose between manifold 2 and 3 
</p><fig id="GUID-65DDB297-434F-40C2-BCFE-C6ADE0732A6D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-38DCA3D1-1A21-4E0B-869D-DCBF2E41705A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-38DCA3D1-1A21-4E0B-869D-DCBF2E41705A-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-E3150BF2-1B5C-4A64-9396-EA65B7E0B5D1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-918C69F0-DBA9-4F77-817C-F3A87CB9CE37-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-918C69F0-DBA9-4F77-817C-F3A87CB9CE37-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-D07890B2-12A0-4AEF-A5F3-A512B0167FB9" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Test failed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Replace the manifold 2. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the 4 red clamps. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Test Manifold 3:</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Place 5 red clamps on the air tube of all printheads (on the part with the sleeve). 
</p><fig id="GUID-6E482887-779E-4294-939E-BC26F5963D7E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C17118E4-5CDF-4488-9F95-BFB3CC653EDD-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C17118E4-5CDF-4488-9F95-BFB3CC653EDD-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3240D9F0-7DA7-4358-9910-40BAE509A6B1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-80C5D8F3-31CC-4132-AC83-0E21DD683459-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-80C5D8F3-31CC-4132-AC83-0E21DD683459-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-6DE978F6-E8D7-4904-8254-824C0349FA75" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Test failed: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Replace manifold 3. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">16 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Remove the 5 red clamps. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">17 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Close the 4 or 5 (white) clamps on the air hose to the 4 printheads. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-4BA040BB-2038-4450-BF02-9F2D153D1E45" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-70D88202-8409-4F9A-8D5F-8DF157FFCC1A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-70D88202-8409-4F9A-8D5F-8DF157FFCC1A-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">18 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Do 
<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref>. 
</p><note id="GUID-4374DED5-DC9B-47AA-AF66-5459A5CBD830" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> If Test Failed: One or more filters are leaking. Goto step 17 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">19 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">If test failed : 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">A) Place 5 (red) clamps before the filters 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">B) Open 1 (red) clamp 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">C) Do<xref keyref="SDS07-6-004" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-ED87B00A-C62B-43E0-8313-AE55741AC42F.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07-6-004 Check pressure leakage?>07-6-004 Check pressure leakage [Special Tests]</xref> 
</p><note id="GUID-682E5B41-54EE-4B9B-99A8-E0D85305F8EA" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> Test should be performed with the Manifolds set to "OFF". (manifold open)
</p></note><p class="- topic/p ">D) Repeat step B/C/D until a leaking air filter is found. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">E) Replace air filter. Open the 4 or 5 (white) clamps. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> F) Remove all Red clamps 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> G) Open the 4 or 5 (white) clamps. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-19746459-8D6F-4094-8203-936D221312D9.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>